race.comment: CHERGUI (1) is a promising gelding who has come back well as a 3yo. He started odds-on fresh at Seymour but just found one too good, and that horse (Ludlum) was heavily backed in a Listed race at Flemington next time out. CHERGUI then took care of his maiden easily at Ballarat when sent forward and a similar ride will see him very hard to beat again. EXCENIA (6) has just found one better in both runs this time in, just missing at Geelong last time out. She's been given a let-up since then with improvement to come and can challenge late. ALL PINK (9) was just fair fresh when in the market but has ability and could improve. BLAZE AWAY (3) is off a tidy maiden win, next best.
